Summer Founders Program offers $15,000 to student startup teams

The 2020 Summer Founders program provides selected Penn State entrepreneurial teams (founders) $15,000 to work full time on their startup, social good or nonprofit idea. Working over the summer, the program provides workspace and a plethora of resources and support.

Penn State physicists earn second place in annual Buchalter Cosmology Prize

Three Penn State physicists earned second place in 2019 Buchalter Cosmology Prize, which was announced at the 235th meeting of the American Astronomical Society on Jan. 6 in Honolulu, Hawaii. The annual prize seeks to reward new ideas or discoveries that have the potential to produce a breakthrough advance in the understanding of the origin, structure and evolution of the universe.
